{"word":"ἄορ","slug":"ἄορ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄορ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀείρω'><el>ἀείρω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ᾰ</el> in <a href='S:ἄορ'><el>ἄορ</el></a>; but in <a href='S:trisyllable'>trisyll.</a> cases also <el>ᾱ.</el>\n<p/><i>a hanger, sword</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: he also uses a <a href='S:masculine'>masc.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <el>ἄορας.</el><p/>"}]}